The paper discusses a method for scientometric evaluation of multi- or interdisciplinary units, which involves comparing papers in different fields based on their citation behavior. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on citation analysis and research evaluation, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SI, cs.CL, and cs.LG.
